<TITLE> Hasina ready to sit with Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)  Sheikh Hasina is ready to sit with her rival Khaleda Zia but on issue-based discussion, the Awami League's spokesperson said on Wednesday. "Our president is ready for discussion. But that must have an agenda," Syed Ashraful Islam told reporters after Hasina met with three envoys at her Sudha Sadan home. The Awami League president held a meeting for one and a half hours with ambassadors of Italy, the Netherlands and Sweden Wednesday morning. After the meeting Swedish envoy told reporters they hoped that an acceptable election would be held on the declared day with the participation of all parties. They stressed the two leaders should sit for discussions to resolve the thorny issues. Ashraful said: "The December 18 election must be held. It is necessary for a good future of the country." "The country's future is depending on the elections now," he said. "We have told the government a free and fair election should take place with the participation of all parties. People will not accept it if the date is deferred." bdnew
